==English==

===Etymology===
: Latin '''[[nubilis]]''', from '''[[nubere]]''' ((for a woman) to marry); probably akin to Greek '''nymphe''' (bride, nymph), Korean '''[[눕다]]''' (nubda: to lie on one's back) cf. '''[[굽다]]''' (gubda: to lie on, etc.). [You may observe the different bodily poses from those initials, ㄴ and ㄱ, of both Korean words.] 

===Adjective===

'''nubile'''

#Of an age suitable for marriage; marriageable.

